ON=Goodbye
ON=Farewell
	say Goodbye.
	BYE
	return 1
ON=APRON
say Big, burly blacksmiths wear these types of aprons.
ON=CAPE
ON=COAT
say Everyone should have a cape.  It completes the whole look.
ON=CLOTH
ON=CLOTHES
ON=CLOTHING
say Clothes express who you are.  And you... has a few issues...
ON=CLOTHIER
say Oh, that's just a way fancy tailor.
ON=DRESS
say Funny that you mentions that.  I just made a lovely dress of silk.
ON=GARMENT
say What type of garment does you speak of?
ON=KILT
say I have kilts in plaid and... well... plaid.
ON=PANT
say I can tailor any pants that you has.
ON=ROBE
say Robes are very popular these days.
ON=SEW
say Of course I can sew.  What a silly question!
ON=SHAWL
say Shawls are for grandmothers.  You needs a cape.
ON=SHIRT
say I do have a few fine silk shirts.
ON=SKILL
ON=THREAD
say I can sew up any item you wish.  Perhaps a nice beret or sash then?
ON=SKIRT
say A well made skirt can really catch the eye.  If that's the look you desires...
ON=TAILOR
	say Of course I'm a Tailor.  It was my calling in life.
ON=VEST
	sayu I don't care for vests, they make me look pudgy.
//RANDOM=Thread, buttons and bows.  Tailoring isn't job, but a calling.

[SPEECH jobTailorMaster]
//GUILDMASTER Clothier
ON=Hail
ON=Hi
ON=Greet
ON=Hello
	say Greetings, lovely friend!
ON=Job
ON=What do you do
	say I am the best clothier in the land!
ON=Bye
ON=Goodbye
ON=Farewell
	say Until we meet again...
	BYE
