[SPEECH jobMerchantMaster]
//GUILDMASTER Merchant
DEFAULT=I do not understand thee.
ON=Hail
ON=Hi
ON=Greet
ON=Hello
say Greetings.
ON=Job
ON=What do you do
say I am a GuildMaster Merchant, meaning I instruct in the ways of the service trades.
ON=Bye
ON=Goodbye
ON=Farewell
	say Goodbye.
	BYE
	return 1
ON=deaf
ON=hearing
sayu I apologize. We occasionally feature loud bards for entertainment. I fear I am quite deaf!
ON=EMPATH
ON=ABBEY
sayu 'Tis a boring place -- no drinking, no wenches.  Only solitary rooms and books!
ON=ARTIFACT
sayu Our regular bareender is so ancient, we do sometimes refer to him as "The artifact."
ON=BARMAID
sayu Keep your hands off my girlies, friend.
ON=TAVERN
ON=ALE
ON=BEER
sayu Our beer's the best!  If you'd like watered down horse spit, try some other tavern.
ON=FOOD
ON=BREAKFAST
ON=DINNER
ON=LUNCH
sayu Nothing like good food to help digest ale!
ON=HINT
ON=INFO
sayu We serve fine food and drink.  For more help than that, may I suggest you call a GM?
ON=MAGIC
sayu If I catch anyone creating food with magic, I'll be quite upset. It undercuts our market.
ON=NEWS
sayu I hear the pie is excellent today!
ON=ITCH
ON=SCRATCH
ON=RUMOR
ON=RUMOUR
sayu I wasn't going to mention it, but do be careful in your choice of wenches.  Some may leave you itchy.
ON=TO DO
sayu I have to remember to see a doctor about this itch...
ON=WAITRESS
sayu Keep your hands to yourself.  The wenches are for the wenching, waitresses for the uh.. waiting.
ON=WENCH
sayu Oh the finest wenches this side of Empath Abbey, friend!  You may have to haggle for a good price.
ON=WHERE<ANY>MONKS
sayu This is not a holy place.  Try the abbey.
ON=GUILD
sayu Our guild is rarely open to new members. Business is good.
ON=MASTER
say I am indeed a master, meaning I know more of Merchant ways than you may ever hope to.
ON=JOIN
say So you want to get in on the racket, eh?
//RANDOM=Not everyone is cut out for the service trade.


[SPEECH jobFighter]
//FIGHTER
DEFAULT=I do not understand thee.
ON=Hi
ON=Hello
ON=Greet
ON=Hail
say I greet thee.
ON=Bye
ON=Goodbye
ON=Hail
	say Farewell.
	BYE
	return 1
ON=PLATE
ON=ARMOR
say Plate Armor's the best, but requires great strength.  Leather is for weaklings.
ON=AXE
sayu Alyough the Executioner's Axe is most feared, the Double Axe lasts longer and inflicts more damage.
ON=HALBERD
ON=BARDICHE
sayu The Bardiche lasts longer in battle than the Halberd, but does less damage.
ON=CROSSBOW
ON=BOW
sayu A regular bow can be a better albeit less powerful friend than the more unweildy Crossbow.
ON=NORSE HELM
ON=OPEN FACED HELM
ON=HELM
sayu Of the plain helms available, a closed helm will provide the best protection in battle.
ON=BUCKLER
sayu Don't be fooled. A buckler offers little more protection that the shorter-lived wooden shield.
ON=CHAIN
sayu While chain is more easily damaged than ringmail, it offers better protection.
ON=CLUB
sayu Clubs are often the weapon of choice for stupid creatures.
ON=SCIMITAR
ON=CUTLASS
sayu Only the scimitar equals the slashing speed of a cutlass.
ON=FIGHT
sayu I always try to be prepared for battle, so I keep my armor clean and a weapon at the ready.
ON=FORK
sayu A pitchfork may be faster, but for my money, only a war fork is sure to leave 'em screaming.
ON=GAUNTLET
sayu Gauntlets are better protection for the wrists.
ON=GORGET
sayu The gauntlet may seem small protection for the neck, it is thick and protective.
ON=HEATER
sayu The heater shield offers stylish but average protection.
ON=THOU<ANY>IDIOT
ON=STUPID
ON=MORON
ON=IDIOT
ON=YOU<ANY>IDIOT
ON=THOU<ANY>
ON=YOU<ANY>MORON
sayu Be careful, friend, or I shall have to prove my sword is sharper than your tongue.
ON=KILL
say Oh I just love killing.
ON=KATANA
ON=KITANA
say This sword does little damage compared with the broad sword.
ON=KRYSS
say The kryss does more damage and lasts longer than the quick slashing butcher knife.
ON=MAUL
ON=MACE
sayu In the mace family, a war mace or war hammer will hurt your opponent most.
ON=MAIM
sayu Maiming is almost as good as killing. Almost.
ON=PROVISIONS
sayu See a provisioner for supplies if you're going on a long battle journey.
ON=RING
sayu Most rings are ordinary, but I have heard of special rings which increase one's strength in battle.
ON=SHIELD
sayu The Chaos Shield yields more protection than the Order Shield.
ON=SKILL
sayu Some weapons require great skill in a given area, like Swordsmanship, Fencing or Mace Fighting.
ON=SPEAR
sayu Bah. Spears better for catching fish.
ON=STAFF
sayu A black staff does more damage than a gnarled staff, but isn't as fast.
ON=SWORD
sayu A long sword is my favorite weapon for damage and it requires less frequent repairs than the faster cutlass.
ON=TROUBLE
sayu It seems you are expert at getting yourself into trouble.
ON=WEAPON
sayu My favorite weapons are those which do the most damage!
